The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	 Former Bengal captain Deep Dasgupta will be joining the final Kolkata Knight Riders camp for a trial.       
	The camp will commence from February 27.       
	With Brendon McCullum unavailable during the first phase of the tournament and Wriddhiman Saha not in best of forms, Deeps experience of playing for Twenty20 for ICL team Royal Bengal Tigers may just come in handy.                
	 Senior CAB officials will be meeting president Jagmohan Dalmiya after the Eden Test to decide on future course of action against Manoj Tiwary.      
	The Bengal player was cautioned by the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) on Monday for showing dissent on and off the field repeatedly.       
	Right now, we are busy with the Test match but certainly, the senior members will sit down and decide on the next course of action, Dalmiya said on Tuesday.                
	 The three-day West Bengal Ladies Challenge Trophy gets underway at the Royal Calcutta Golf Club on Wednesday. Golfers from around the country will be seen in action during the tourney.                       
